  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A screening sensitivity study was conducted informally to evaluate the influence of viscosity and inlet velocity boundary conditions on the relative hemolysis index; results confirmed low parametric sensitivity across the operating envelope. This screening informed factor-level judgements but was not formalized into a structured sensitivity analysis node.",
