      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, formal use error assessment is not required; analyst qualifications and review processes serve as adequate controls.",
      "rationale": "All simulations were performed by a PhD-level CFD analyst with 8 years of cardiovascular CFD experience. Simulation setup was independently reviewed by a senior analyst. Standard operating procedures for ANSYS Fluent setup were followed. Formal use error factor assessment is not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, model form uncertainty does not require formal quantification; selection rationale and literature support are sufficient.",
      "rationale": "The k-omega SST turbulence model was selected based on published literature demonstrating superior performance for transitional flows in cardiovascular pump geometries. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model is the regulatory standard for CFD hemolysis prediction. Model form selection is supported by literature and expert judgement; formal model form uncertainty quantification is not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
